<h2 class="text-center">Escudella (Mixed Meat Stew)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Mains/Beef-Stew.webp" alt="Beef Stew" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>2 Cups Borlotti Beans (Rinsed)</li>
                        <li>Beef Bones</li>
                        <li>3 Boneless Skinless Chicken Thighs</li>
                        <li>28g Sausage Meat (Rolled Into Small Balls)</li>
                        <li>3 Slices of Thick Ham (Cut Into Chunks)</li>
                        <li>1⁄2 a Cabbage</li>
                        <li>1 Large Potato (Cut Into Large Chunks)</li>
                        <li>1⁄4 Cup Uncooked Rice</li>
                        <li>1 Cup Pasta</li>
                        <li>1 Cup Garbanzo Beans</li>
                        <li>Salt and Pepper to Taste</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Put the beans, sausage balls, ham, chicken and bones into a pot with 8 cups of water and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let it simmer covered for two hours.
                            <br/><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Remove the bones and bring the remaining stock and meat back up to a boil (if there isn't a lot of liquid you can add more water), then add the cabbage, potato, rice, pasta, garbanzo beans, salt and pepper.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Cook for another 30 minutes, or until the potatoes and rice are tender, serve warm ladled into bowls with crusty bread.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

