<h2 class="text-center">Cunillo (Chicken Stew)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"> </div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Mains/Chicken-Stew.webp" alt="Chicken Stew" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>1/4 Cup Vinegar</li>
                        <li>A Few Tarragon leaves</li>
                        <li>2 Chicken Thighs (Skinless and Boneless)</li>
                        <li>1 Cup Chopped Onions</li>
                        <li>1 Tsp Dried Oregano</li>
                        <li>1 Tsp Dried Thyme</li>
                        <li>4 Bay Leaves</li>
                        <li>1 Cup White Wine</li>
                        <li>3 Cups Crushed Tomatoes</li>
                        <li>Salt and Pepper to Taste</li>
                        <li>2 Cups Pasta</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Place the chicken, tarragon leaves and vinegar in a bowl, turn to coat and marinate for 20 to 30 minutes (preferably overnight if possible).
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Place the onions in a slow cooker which has been greased with oil, then arrange the chicken thighs over onions.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Sprinkle oregano, thyme, and bay leaves over the chicken and season to taste. Pour the wine over the chicken, then add the crushed tomatoes.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, or until chicken is tender and falls off the bone. Serve over cooked pasta.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

