<h2 class="text-center">Trucha a La Piedra (Grilled Trout)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Mains/Grilled-Fish.webp" alt="Grilled Fish" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>4 Fresh Rainbow Trout (Cleaned and Deboned)</li>
                        <li>2 Lemons (One Sliced in Rounds the Other in Wedges)</li>
                        <li>8 Sprigs of Fresh Parsley</li>
                        <li>4 Sprigs of Fresh Tarragon </li>
                        <li>4 Sprigs of Fresh Oregano</li>
                        <li>4 Slices of Bacon</li>
                        <li>Salt and Pepper to Taste</li>
                        <li>Olive oil</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Preheat a grill to a medium heat, season the interior of the trout and stuff with the parsley, tarragon, oregano and a slice of lemon.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Then rub the exterior of the trout with olive oil, place a slice of bacon on top and cook on each side on a baking tray until nicely charred on each side.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Garnish with the left over parsley springs and lemon wedges and serve with a drizzle of olive oil.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

