<h2 class="text-center">Cannelloni Andorrana (Andorran Style Cannelloni)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br /><br />    
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Andorra/Mains/Cannelloni.webp" alt="Cannelloni" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <h2 class="text-left">Ingredients</h2>
                    <div class="text-left">
                        <h3>For the Filling</h3>
                    </div>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>400g Minced Lamb</li>
                        <li>150g Feta Cheese</li>
                        <li>100g Cream Cheese</li>
                        <li>Salt and Pepper to Taste</li>
                        <li>8 Cooked Lasagne Sheets</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left">
                        <h3>For the Sauce</h3>
                    </div>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>250ml (1 Cup) Beef Stock</li>
                        <li>100g Milk</li>
                        <li>2 Tbsp Butter</li>
                        <li>2 Tbsp Flour</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left">
                        <h3>For the Topping</h3>
                    </div>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>200g Grated Cheese</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Preheat the oven to 200 C and brown the meat in a pan with salt and pepper. Once the meat is cooked through, remove from heat and mix in the feta cheese and the cream cheese.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Place the mix on the lasagne sheets and roll them then place the filled and rolled sheets into an ovenproof dish.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Melt the butter in a pot, and stir in the flour until the mix is even, then add the milk and stock while stirring. Add a little at a time to get a smoother mixture, bring to a boil while stirring, and pour the sauce over the rolled sheets in the ovenproof dish.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Top the dish with grated cheese, and bake on the middle rack for 10—20 minutes until the cheese is golden brown. Serve with a side salad.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

